Description: automatic SUID, SGID, capabilities and sudo privilege escalation
 bINsUID automates enumeration and exploitation of common Linux privilege
 escalation vectors: SUID/SGID binaries, file and process capabilities,
 passwordless sudo rules (including SETENV), writable PATH directories,
 cron persistence surfaces, and privileged group membership.
 .
 Findings are ranked by priority and matched against bundled offline
 GTFOBins data with built-in automatic payloads. Intended for authorized
 penetration testing, CTF challenges, and security training.
